cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.NE 

The paper describes a computational model of cultural evolution based on neural network agents that evolve ideas for actions through invention and imitation. This suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) as the primary sub-categories. The paper also discusses the cognitive mechanisms underlying cultural evolution, which could fall under the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SD) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the use of neural networks suggests a potential connection to neural computation and neuroscience (cs.NE).
